. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4D6AF2F6E9956317C1B869" authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1914" box="[2325,2497,826,859]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="182" pageNumber="944" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caucensis">M. caucensis</taxonomicName>
was revalidated as a distinct species by R. Moratelli and colleagues in 2013, which included a comprehensive discussion about nomenclature of the 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4D6AF2F71E9581178BB8CB" baseAuthorityName="Schinz" baseAuthorityYear="1821" box="[2274,2443,984,1017]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="182" pageNumber="944" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigricans">M. nigricans</taxonomicName>
