Colombian Black 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4D6AF2F82C913D162ABCB7" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[2000,2090,1892,1925]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="182" pageNumber="944" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
are aerial insectivores, foraging in forested habitats and over water.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
